<metal:main use-macro="load: default.pt">
    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="content_title">
        Rossum's Battle of Bits -- &alpha;
    </tal:block>   

    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="menu_items">
        <li class="dropdown">
            <a href="#" class="dropdown-toggle" data-toggle="dropdown">Games <b class="caret"></b></a>
            <ul class="dropdown-menu">
                <li><a href="#">Connect</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </tal:block>

    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="content_body">
        <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row-fluid">    
           
        <div class="span9">    
        <h2>Brief introduction</h2>
        <p>
        This project is a virtual battlefield for long standing battles of wits between artificial intelligences.
        This project is also fills the void left behind
        <a href="http://aichallenge.org/" title="The Google AI Challenge Home Page">The Google AI Challenge</a>.
        There are few key differences between <em>The Google AI Challenge</em> and
        <em>Rossum's Battle of Bits</em> (<em>RBoB</em>):
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li> There are no restrictions on the language, libraries or techniques used in <em>RBoB</em>.
            Instead of uploading your code on our server, your bot communicates with the server
            via TCP connection.
            </li>
            <li> There are no deadlines in <em>RBoB</em>.
            Instead of short term tournaments, there are longstanding ratings.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
        The repertoire of games offered by <em>RBoB</em> is ever-expanding.
        </p>

        </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </tal:block>
</metal:main>

